trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProvider"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
The BuildProviderCollection is used to compile custom resource files.
You can have any number of build providers.
The BuildProviderCollection does not refer to any actual element in the underlying configuration file.
It is a construct that allows easy access to the compilation information it contains.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProviderCollection"></xref> class.
Adds a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProvider"></xref> object to the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProviderCollection"></xref>.
If the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.BuildProvider> object already exists in the collection, the build provider is ignored.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProvider"></xref> object.
Clears all <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProvider"></xref> objects from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProviderCollection"></xref>.
